    "description_long": "This object is a small graveyard ensemble featuring several distinct tombstones, grave markers, and a section of cemetery fencing. The set includes a prominent Celtic cross monument, two rectangular gravestones with raised platforms, a smaller upright headstone, and a flat grave slab. A wrought iron fence section with stone pillars and a cross-topped post marks the cemetery boundary, adding a sense of enclosure. The surfaces are weathered, with a mossy, aged stone appearance and darkened metal on the fence. The overall arrangement suggests a historical or traditional cemetery, with each element crafted from stone or metal and showing signs of exposure to the elements.",
